{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"MIC","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Micah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Micah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Micah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Micah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Micah"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Judgment to Come"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/7.htm#17|>Isaiah 7:17–25</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word of the LORD that came to Micah the Moreshite in the days of Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah —  what he saw regarding Samaria and Jerusalem: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Hear, O peoples, all of you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["listen, O earth, and everyone in it! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["May the Lord GOD bear witness against you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the Lord from His holy temple. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For behold, the LORD comes forth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from His dwelling place; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will come down and tread "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["on the high places of the earth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The mountains will melt beneath Him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the valleys will split apart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like wax before the fire, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like water rushing down a slope. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"All this is for the transgression of Jacob "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the sins of the house of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What is the transgression of Jacob? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Is it not Samaria? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And what is the high place of Judah? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Is it not Jerusalem? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Therefore I will make Samaria "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a heap of rubble in the open field, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a planting area for a vineyard. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will pour her stones into the valley "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and expose her foundations. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"All her carved images will be smashed to pieces; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["all her wages will be burned in the fire, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and I will destroy  all her idols. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Since she collected  the wages of a prostitute, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they will be used again on a prostitute. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Weeping and Mourning"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Because of this I will lament and wail; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will walk barefoot and naked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will howl  like a jackal ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>a serpent</i> or <i>a dragon</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and mourn like an ostrich. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>like daughters of an ostrich</i> or <i>like daughters of an owl</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"For her wound is incurable; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" it has reached  even Judah; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it has approached the gate of my people,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as far as Jerusalem itself. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Do not tell it in Gath; ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Gath</i> sounds like the Hebrew for <i>tell</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"do not weep  at all. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Roll in the dust in Beth-leaphrah. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Beth-leaphrah</i> means <i>house of dust</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Depart in shameful nakedness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["O dwellers of Shaphir. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Shaphir</i> means <i>pleasant</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The dwellers of Zaanan ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Zaanan</i> sounds like the Hebrew for <i>come out</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will not come out. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Beth-ezel ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Beth-ezel</i> means <i>adjoining house</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"is in mourning; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["its support is taken from you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For the dwellers of Maroth ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Maroth</i> sounds like the Hebrew for <i>bitter</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"pined for good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but calamity came down from the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even to the gate of Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Harness your chariot horses, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["O dweller of Lachish. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Lachish</i> sounds like the Hebrew term for <i>team of horses</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You were the beginning of sin to the Daughter of Zion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for the transgressions of Israel were found in you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Therefore, send farewell gifts ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>give dowry</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"to  Moresheth-gath; ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Moresheth</i> sounds like the Hebrew for <i>gift</i> or <i>dowry</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the houses of Achzib ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Achzib</i> means <i>deception</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"will prove deceptive "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to the kings of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"I will again bring a conqueror against you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["O dweller of Mareshah. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Mareshah</i> sounds like the Hebrew for <i>conqueror</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The glory of Israel will come to Adullam. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Shave yourselves bald and cut off your hair "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in mourning for your precious children; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["make yourselves as bald as an eagle, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they will go from you into exile. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Woe to Oppressors"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Woe to those who devise iniquity "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and plot evil on their beds! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["At morning’s light they accomplish it "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because the power is in their hands. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"They covet fields and seize them; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they take away houses. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They deprive a man of his home, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a fellow man of his inheritance. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Therefore this is what the LORD  says: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I am planning against this nation a disaster "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from which you cannot free your necks. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then you will not walk so proudly, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for it will be a time of calamity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"In that day they will take up a proverb against you "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and taunt you with this bitter lamentation : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["We are utterly ruined ! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He has changed the portion of my people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["How He has removed it from me! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He has allotted our fields to traitors. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Therefore, you will have no one in the assembly of the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to divide the land by lot. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Reproof of False Prophets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../ezekiel/13.htm|>Ezekiel 13:1–16</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Do not preach, they preach. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Do not preach these things; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["disgrace will not overtake us. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Should it be said, O house of Jacob, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Is the Spirit of the LORD  impatient? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Are these the things He does? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Do not My words bring good "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to him who walks uprightly? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But of late My people have risen up  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like an enemy: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You strip off the splendid robe "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from unsuspecting passersby "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like men returning from battle. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"You drive the women of My people "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from their pleasant homes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You take away My blessing "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from their children forever. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Arise and depart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for this is not your place of rest, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because its defilement brings destruction— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a grievous destruction! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"If a man of wind were to come "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and say falsely, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will preach to you of wine and strong drink, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>“I will prophesy to you for wine and strong drink”</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he would be just the preacher for this people! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Remnant of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../micah/5.htm#7|>Micah 5:7–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I will surely gather  all of you, O Jacob; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will collect  the remnant of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will bring them together like sheep in a pen, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a flock in the midst of its pasture —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a noisy throng. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"One who breaks open the way "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will go up before them; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they will break through the gate, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and go out by it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Their King will pass through before them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the LORD as their leader. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Rulers and Prophets Condemned"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then I said: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Hear now, O leaders of Jacob, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you rulers of the house of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Should you not  know  justice? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"You hate good and love evil. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You tear the skin from my people "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and strip the flesh from their bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," You eat the flesh of my people "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["after stripping off  their skin  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and breaking their bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You chop them up like flesh for the cooking pot, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like meat in a cauldron. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then they will cry out to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He will not answer them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["At that time He will hide His face from them "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because of the evil they have done. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"This is what the LORD says: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["As for the prophets "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who lead My people astray,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who proclaim peace  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["while they chew with their teeth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but declare war against one "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who puts nothing in their mouths: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Therefore night will come over you without visions, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and darkness without divination. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The sun will set on these prophets, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the daylight will turn black over them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then the seers will be ashamed "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the diviners will be disgraced. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They will all cover  their mouths "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because there is no answer from God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"As for me, however, I am filled with power "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["by the Spirit of the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with justice and courage, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to declare to Jacob his transgression "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and to Israel his sin. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Now hear this, O leaders of the house of Jacob "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and rulers of the house of Israel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who despise justice  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and pervert all that is right, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"who build Zion with bloodshed "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Jerusalem with iniquity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Her leaders judge for a bribe, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["her priests teach for a price, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and her prophets practice divination for money. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yet they lean upon the LORD, saying, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Is not the LORD among us? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["No disaster can come upon us. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Therefore, because of you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Zion will be plowed like a field, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jerusalem will become a heap of rubble, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the temple mount a wooded ridge. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Mountain of the House of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/2.htm|>Isaiah 2:1–4</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," In the last days the mountain of the house of the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will be established as the chief of the mountains; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it will be raised above the hills, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the peoples will stream to it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And many nations will come and say: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Come, let us go up to the mountain of the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to the house of the God of Jacob. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will teach us His ways, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so that we may walk in His paths. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For the law will go forth from Zion "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then He will judge between many peoples "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and arbitrate for strong  nations far and wide. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then they will beat their swords into plowshares "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and their spears into pruning hooks. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Nation will no longer take up the sword against nation, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["nor will they train anymore for war. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And each man will sit under his own vine "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and under his own fig tree, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with no one to frighten him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For the mouth of the LORD of Hosts has spoken. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Though all  the nations "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["may walk in the name of their gods, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["yet we will walk in the name of the LORD our God "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["forever and ever. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Restoration of Zion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../zechariah/8.htm|>Zechariah 8:1–23</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"On that day, declares the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will gather the lame; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will assemble the outcast, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even those whom I have afflicted. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And I will make  the lame into a remnant, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the outcast into a strong nation. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then the LORD will rule over them in Mount Zion "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from that day and forever . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And you, O watchtower of the flock, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["O stronghold ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>hill</i>; Hebrew <i>And you, Migdal-eder, the Ophel</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"of the Daughter of Zion —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the former dominion will be restored to you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["sovereignty will come to the Daughter of Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Why do you now cry aloud? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Is there no king among you? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Has your counselor perished "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so that anguish grips you like a woman in labor? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Writhe in agony, O Daughter of Zion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a woman in labor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For now you will leave the city "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and camp in the open fields. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You will go to Babylon; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["there you will be rescued; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["there the LORD will redeem you "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the hand of your enemies! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But now many nations "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["have assembled against you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["saying, Let her be defiled, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" and let us feast our eyes on Zion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But they do not know the thoughts of the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or understand His plan, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for He has gathered them "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like sheaves to the threshing floor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Rise and thresh, O Daughter of Zion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for I will give you horns of iron "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and hooves  of bronze "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to break to pieces many peoples. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then you will devote ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>devote to destruction</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"their gain to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["their wealth to the Lord of all the earth. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Ruler from Bethlehem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../matthew/2.htm|>Matthew 2:1–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now, O daughter of troops, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["mobilize your troops; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for a siege is laid against us! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["With a rod they will strike  the cheek  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of the judge of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"But you,  Bethlehem Ephrathah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who are small among the clans ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>thousands</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"of Judah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["out of you will come forth for Me "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["One to be ruler over Israel ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in Matthew 2:6"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["One whose origins are of old, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the days of eternity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Therefore Israel will be abandoned "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["until  she who is in labor has given birth; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["then the rest of His brothers will return "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to the children of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"He will stand and shepherd His flock "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the strength of the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the majestic name of the LORD His God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And they will dwell securely, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for then His greatness will extend "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to the ends of the earth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And He will be our peace ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>their peace</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when Assyria invades our land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and tramples our citadels. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["We will raise against it seven shepherds, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even eight leaders of men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And they will rule  the land of Assyria with the sword, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the land of Nimrod with the blade drawn. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So He will deliver us "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when Assyria invades our land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and marches into our borders. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Remnant of Jacob"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../micah/2.htm#12|>Micah 2:12–13</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then the remnant of Jacob will be "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the midst of many peoples "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like dew from the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like showers on the grass, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["which do not wait for man "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or linger for mankind . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Then the remnant of Jacob will be among the nations, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the midst of many peoples, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a lion among the beasts of the forest, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a young lion among flocks of sheep, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["which tramples and tears as it passes through, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with no one to rescue them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Your hand will be lifted over your foes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and all your enemies will be cut off. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," In that day, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will remove your horses from among you "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and wreck your chariots. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"I will remove the cities of your land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and tear down all your strongholds. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I will cut the sorceries from your hand, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and you will have no fortune-tellers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"I will also cut off the carved images "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and sacred pillars from among you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so that you will no longer bow down "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to the work of your own hands. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I will root out the Asherah poles from your midst "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and demolish your cities. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"I will take vengeance  in anger and wrath "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["upon the nations that have not obeyed Me. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Case against Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Hear now  what the LORD says: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Arise, plead your case before the mountains, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and let the hills hear your voice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Hear, O mountains, the LORD’s indictment , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you enduring foundations of the earth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For the LORD has a case against His people, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and He will argue it against Israel: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"My people, what have I done to you? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Testify against Me how I have wearied you! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For I brought you up from the land of Egypt "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and redeemed you from the house of slavery. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I sent Moses before you,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as well as Aaron and Miriam. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"My people, remember  what Balak king of Moab counseled "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and what Balaam son of Beor answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Remember your journey from Shittim ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Acacia Grove</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"to Gilgal, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so that you may acknowledge the righteousness of the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"With what shall I come before the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when I bow before the God on high? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Should I come to Him with burnt offerings, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with year-old  calves? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Would the LORD be pleased with thousands of rams, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with ten thousand rivers of oil? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Shall I present my firstborn for my transgression, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the fruit of my body for the sin of my soul? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"He has shown you, O man, what is good. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And what does the LORD require of you  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but to act justly, to love mercy, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and to walk humbly with your God? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Punishment of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The voice of the LORD calls out to the city "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and it is sound wisdom to fear Your name): "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Heed the rod "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the One who ordained it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Can I forget any longer , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["O house of the wicked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the treasures of wickedness "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the short ephah, which is accursed? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Can I excuse dishonest scales "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or bags of false weights? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For the wealthy of the city "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["are full of violence, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and its residents speak lies; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["their tongues are deceitful in their mouths. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Therefore I am striking you severely, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to ruin you because of your sins. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"You will eat but not be satisfied, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your hunger will remain with you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What you acquire, you will not preserve; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and what you save, I will give to the sword. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"You will sow but not reap; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you will press olives but not anoint yourselves with oil; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you will tread grapes but not drink the wine. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"You have kept the statutes of Omri "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and all the practices of Ahab’s house; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you have followed their counsel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Therefore I will make you a desolation, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your inhabitants an object of contempt; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you will bear the scorn of the nations. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX; Hebrew <i>scorn of My people</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Israel’s Great Misery"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../matthew/10.htm#34|>Matthew 10:34–39</a>; <a href =|../luke/12.htm#49|>Luke 12:49–53</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Woe is me! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For I am like one gathering summer fruit "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at the gleaning of the vineyard; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["there is no cluster to eat, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["no early fig that I crave. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The godly man has perished from the earth; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["there is no one upright among men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They all lie in wait for blood; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they hunt one  another with a net. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," Both hands are skilled at evil; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the prince and the judge demand a bribe. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When the powerful utters his evil desire, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they all conspire together. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The best of them is like a brier; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the most upright is sharper than a hedge of thorns. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The day for your watchmen has come, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the day of your visitation. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>your punishment</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Now is the time of their confusion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Do not rely on a friend; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not trust in a companion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Seal the doors of your mouth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from her who lies in your arms. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>in your bosom</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"For a son dishonors his father, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a daughter rises against her mother, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["A man’s enemies are the members "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of his own household. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in Matthew 10:35–36; see also Luke 12:53."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Israel’s Confession and Comfort"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"But as for me, I will look to the LORD; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will wait for the God of my salvation. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["My God will hear me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Do not gloat over me, my enemy! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Though I have fallen, I will arise; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["though I sit in darkness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the LORD will be my light "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Because I have sinned against Him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I must endure the rage of the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["until  He argues my case "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and executes justice for me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will bring me into the light; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will see His righteousness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then my enemy will see "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and will be covered with shame —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she who said to me, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Where is the LORD your God? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["My eyes will see her; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at that time she will be trampled "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like mud in the streets. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"The day for rebuilding your walls will come —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the day for extending your boundary. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"On that day they will come to you "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from Assyria and the cities of Egypt, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even from Egypt to the Euphrates, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>the River</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from sea to sea and mountain to mountain. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then the earth will become desolate "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because of its inhabitants, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as the fruit of their deeds. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>God’s Compassion on Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Shepherd with Your staff Your people, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the flock of Your inheritance. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They live alone in a woodland, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["surrounded by pastures. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>in a woodland, in the midst of Carmel</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Let them graze in Bashan and Gilead, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as in the days of old. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"As in the days when you came out  of Egypt, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will show My wonders. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Nations will see and be ashamed, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["deprived of all their might. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They will put their hands over their mouths, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and their ears will become deaf. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"They will lick the dust like a snake, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like reptiles slithering on the ground. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They will come trembling from their strongholds "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the presence of the LORD our God; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they will tremble in fear of You. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Who is a God like You, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who pardons iniquity "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and passes over the transgression "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of the remnant of His inheritance —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who does not retain His anger forever, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because He delights in loving devotion? ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Forms of the Hebrew <i>chesed</i> are translated here and in most cases throughout the Scriptures as <i>loving devotion</i>; the range of meaning includes <i>love</i>, <i>goodness</i>, <i>kindness</i>, <i>faithfulness</i>, and <i>mercy</i>, as well as <i>loyalty to a covenant</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"He will again have compassion on us; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will vanquish our iniquities. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You will cast out all our sins "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["into the depths of the sea. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"You will show faithfulness to Jacob "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and loving devotion to Abraham, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as You swore to our fathers "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the days of old. "]}]}